items.text: It's now renovated and open now since March 1 2012
Teh peng (iced milk tea). Luck Seng #01-31 pre-mixes the milk tea and stores it in bottles in his fridge. When u order, it's served over ice & is super chilled. Thoughtful!
02-20 Gui Yuan Gong Shan Zhong rojak stall is dishonest. Charged us $6 for cuttlefish only without rojak.
Painting renovation from 2 Mar till 19 Mar. All stores are shut down.
Tiong Bahru Lor Mee #01-15 very good !
Hock Ann prawn noodle is gd...
Cheap food for your picking. Try the desserts for the finale.
Cat train was here!!! Www.sgbinky.com
Love the ice lemon tea at stall # 01-285
If you like Fried Bee Hoon, try Yip Economical Bee Hoon at #01-33. They fry up a decent dish and serves it with the traditional chilli sauce not the nasi lemak type you find commonly in other places.
The economic rice stall @ 01-44 (一定好）sells very good mixed rice with freshly cooked ingredients. Value for $$$ too!
Late night dinner: S$2.50 only with not bad Fish Balls Bak Chor Mee @ #01-45 (next to the Yu Zhi Jia BBQ).
Very nice carrot cake. Both black and white are to die for.
Many yummy food eg fish head bee hoon, western food, yong tau foo etc
I recommend the carrot cake here~! 😍 Parking slots are full on weekends, more slots @ Blk 124A multi-storey carpark instead 👈
pork porridge nice sellin at night #01
Reopened! Cooler, brighter, and can seat more!
The fish ball noodle stall at the corner is really good. Homemade fish balls received my two thumbs up!
We western stall!
Fragrant & refreshing Muar Sugarcane juice from Qing Tian Coffee Stall #01-43. Nice :-9
Really good sambal sting ray
Try the yong tau foo here, long queue expected~ open from midnight only!
Tori Karrage ramen from SAMS KITCHEN is nice.
Western food is great!
Sell alot of nice food
Must try the bukit merah view carrot cake #01-279
The Thai food stall is pretty good
Lor mee long queue
Cheap desserts at 古早剉冰 #01-13. Very smooth ice
Wantan mee: Impressed by big kailan vege portion served w WTM by Depot Road #01-84. Honeyed char siew slices were also generous. They give a mix of boiled & fried wantans. Sauce is mushroom-based
323 has the best kaya butter toast!!
#stervylicious #friedcarrotcake - tried the stall that has great white carrot cake but only I m tasting their black dish. Gotta try - bukit merah view carrot cake /#01-37
Try the Chinese Mutton Soup.
Opp food court coffee shop hock chew tim sum hand madeon d spot....vy gd.....
ChengTeng 80 cents only got red bean some more!
Helang Emas nasi ayam madu must try
Order your drinks from Ah Koon or Ling Ling at 361 Cafe!
Must try the yong tau foo at #01-397. closes on Monday, open around 11pm or later. Long queue.
Hock Ann Prawn Noodle/Lor Mee yummy!
Fruit Juice stall #01-73 is very nice! Got plenty of variety and they even have an accumulative coupon card where you can get a free drink after 10 drinks.
Hai San Chicken Rice is excellent!
Kaya roti: Heng Heng Coffee #01-23 may command a q in d mornings but after a bite, I was unimpressed by d thin spread of kaya, which also lacked any pandan fragrance. Half-boiled eggs were overcooked
nice chicken rice store here
Lor mee n prawn mee is nice
Cheap and nice desserts at Qing Tian Dessert stall, must try!
Long Ji Da Pai Dang #01-68 for salted egg yolk pork rib
R&D wanton noodles is really not bad
Thai is good here.  Corner stall. Tried the basil chicken.  Spicy and licking good 😛
Chai Chuan Tou Yang Rou Tang 柴船头羊肉汤very nice
Handmade Tai Bao from the vendor in the Hawker Centre is good but unfortunately doesn't have ideal packing for takeaway in quality 😤 BYO if you plan to takeaway 👍
Drinks at luck seng coffee stall is awesome! Esp their home made almond lemon tea!
sugarcane drink stall at #01-25 now sells sugarcane drink at $1.20 (up by 20 cents) and smaller cup :(
Mutton soup is great
323 stall's Salmon set at $4.80 is a really value for money deal
Close one week for cleaning.
#01-84 depot road wanton mee us generous with the portion. Tastes good too!
Love the carrot cake here !!
The sambal stingray, Sotong and la la in 鱼之家 is freaking awesome !!
The fish soup stall here is great! Got to try it!
Hong xing fish ball noodles at #01-07. Excellent!

Try the carrot cake, add egg (for both white and black versions)! Thou the black version is not fried evenly, I think the additional egg can help pull the flavors together. But the kueh is really so f
POSB ATM nearby, at next block 117, hidden behind lift lobby A
柴船頭Mutton soup the best in Singapore. 好滿意小籠包another worth going stall for 鍋貼
The wee western damn nice! Must try!!
The fried oysters over here is quite delicious.
Awesome fish soup stall at the far end. Look out for it!
Try the dessert, cheap and good to round up your meal.
Carrot cake is nice
Great World Fishball noodle at #01-30 sells rather good curry chicken ! business is quite good !
The carrot cake is good.  So not, I repeat,  do not,  buy the herbal soup two stores from Bukit Merah View Carrot Cake.  My soup was cold and gross
Prata. Enjoyed my prata from 786 (stall #01-72). Attracted to it initially due to locals queuing up for this stall (instead of the others). Prata was chewy & not oily. Stallholders are a friendly lot
Qing tian ice lemon tea is a must try
Tips?! Ah here is the tip.
Must try BBQ chicken wings dip with super nice chili sauce.
Must try the 'Fa Ji Shu Shi's' vegetarian bee hoon! Generous portion and delicious!
Stall 786!
Carrot cake store beside the happy duck is good
I LOVE THE $1 chawanmushi at 323 new fusion cusine!!!!!
Market going upgrade for 9 months in Jun. Wonder all those old & good uncles still cooking after upgrade. Will sg lose the old taste?
The we western stall is really good. Huge servings and delicious! Do try it if you are here! :)
Weng Kee Hainan Boneless Chicken Rice... BEST...
Try one of best carrot cake at  01-37 红山景菜头粿。
Must try the lor mee and prawn noodle @ Old Fukien Noodles.
Desserts here are cheap
Stall 323 Coffee and Drinks sells very nice steamed bread with butter and kaya
Century egg porridge is nice. So is the duckie rice at blk 116. Cheap also. :D
Carrot cake: While enjoyg plate fr Bukit Merah View Carrot Cake #01-37, discovered their lineage! Chk out Dr Leslie Tay's http://ieatishootipost.sg/2010/02/bukit-merah-view-carrot-cake-last.html
The tong tao hoo here is very very nice.. Much try.. :)
Lai Heng #01-06 has good carrot cake.
Soon Li Yong Tau Foo always long queue.
Bukit Merah Nasi lemak is tasty! Giv alot of rice as well
Can't believe we have an authentic Thai food in this hawker centre! I've try the Thai fried rice set. All I can say is 'two thumbs up'!! 👍👍die die must try!
Love the food here, very cheap
The satay bee hoon is a must try !
The carrot cake there damn nice.
786 Char Kway Teow. Best HALAL Char Kway Teow. Stall usually closed during prayer time.
323 chicken cutlet value for money.wild wild west might be preferred by those who prefer more bland taste
Wantan mee. Locals in the neighbourhood seem to like Kim Huat #01-05. Noodles r chewy, wantans substantial. Ask for more vege & they'll oblige. Soup is tasty but tongue had a buzz, prob due to MSG
Nice fishball noodles!!

One of my late night SOP here: Hock Ann Prawn Noodle & Bee Hoon Soup (S$3) +Chicken Wing from Bt Merah Nasi Lemak (S$1.20) +Muar Sugarcane Juice (S$1.50) +Carpark 30mins (S$0.50). Price has increased!
Late night dinner place with ample open space carpark ;-)
Muslim food here is so horrible. Ordered rojak & tulang merah. But end up with dissapointment. Rojak gravy was tasteless. Soup tulang merah taste more like curry.. & the bone, there's nothing inside.
must eat the carrot cake & 荣華魚圓面 + fish cake...good! if u r not ordering the drinks beside it, then don't sit outside the pavement,many times ppl kana scolded by the drink stall owner...
Carrot cake I like. Drinks are particular cheap too.
Chicken Rice too good.
must try the duck rice! beside the carrot cake stall!
Must try the BBQ stringray and sotong, stall besides the dessert stall
01-72 makes their own apom.
Must try the Yu Zhi Jia yummy
Order a plate of wanton mee. There are a few stalls around and they are all good.
The duck rice next to the carrot cake stall is awesome!
